    <CareerDetail id="jonasRedmann" type="Project" startedOn="12/2008" finishedOn="02/2011 " duration="27M">
      <Institution caption="Jonas&amp;Redmann" field="Machine Ind." size="500-1000 Emp."></Institution>
      <Tasks>
        <Task>
          <Summary>Visualization Framework Development</Summary>
          <Detail>Research, analysis, design and development of a Visualization Design &amp; Runtime Framework for the Rapid-HMI-Development for the Photovoltaic Wafer Production Machines. Active cooperation with the company on an Interface Development for a High-Tech Measurement-Instrument.</Detail>
          <Detail>The framework is built on more than 70 re-useable components, an ORM based and data binding supported data interface to the PLC and an integrated extendable Design-Environment(IDE). The ORM-Capability of the data-interface supported by a Code-Generator , in order to generate DAO-Code from data structures of the PLC instantly. Access to PLC happens asynchronously to reduce latencies.</Detail>
          <Detail>The Framework replaced Siemens WinCC / Protool Platform.</Detail>
          <Detail>The User-Interface was designed to be translucent and touch-screen capable/optimized. Performance demanding core-functions was written in Assembler using SSE and MMX extensions to maximize hardware utilization.</Detail>
          <Detail>Painting/Drawing outsourced to separate renderer classes(Decorator Pattern), which enables / simplifies Corporate-Designs(so-called Skins) and customizations.</Detail>
          <Detail>The resources (icons, etc.) will be accessed through in DFM hardcoded URLs, which allows design-time-environment to be almost same like runtime, which increases RAD capabilities sharply. This was done by developing a Async.-Pluggable-Protocol-Handler as COM-Server using WININET APIs.</Detail>
        </Task>
        <Task>
          <Summary>Basler Interface Development</Summary>
          <Detail>Design and lead the development of series of interfaces between an optical high-tech measurement device from company Tordivel/Basler and PLC(Twincat) device using .NET as development platform.</Detail>
          <Detail>The communication between parts made through RPC(.NET Remoting).</Detail>
        </Task>
